And supermodel</span><br>  Posts: 417<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/8/03 1:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=141>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Arch Lich : Good Rotation <br>
Cursed Cleanup : Good Rotation <br>
Trakanon: Bad<br>
Severilous: Bad<br>
<br>
**No I'm not gonna go through each and every rotation that this server has , and state what I think of it**<br>
<br>
There are some others that are approaching the level where they are starting to fill up... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Your basis for deciding good and bad rotations is way off base.  The more people you have interested in content the more you *need* rotations.  Severillous, before he was on rotation, was seen by a small handful of guilds – guilds that were capable of moving in with 1-2 groups, killing him, and even if they didn’t need the scale or haste items, they can sell them for 60k+ plat each (not counting rare spells like Torpor or Sunstrike).  20 minutes of work, and your guild is doing well for peridots and pearls for a few weeks.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What is so inherently bad , about allowing Guilds that have the man power to go kill a mob whenever it up ((Let me finish)) ... Right now on Trakanon and Severilous there is a HUGE bottleneck there.... Anyone remember the Discussions on Ragefire rotations etc. And How bad that got ... Yes that was more vocal ... but you are looking at the exact same thing. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What is so inherently bad is that if you take Severillous off rotation, no guild that is currently on rotation would ever see him again.  You’d have smaller groups of the big guilds park a toon with sense summoned in the zone and pop him every time they saw him up.  Please see the hundreds of Lodizal kills for an idea of what FFA mobs look like, and keep in mind, Lodi shields don’t sell for anywhere near what a CoF or Green scale or Torpor do.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>IF I'm in a Guild (note I'm making an example)and we have the man power and mobolization to go take out a mob fast, sure for a while , we will probably do just that ... And Yes other Guilds might not see the mob for a while ... But eventually other guilds will because my Guild will loose interest in the mob as its something that we no longer need , and we will move on ... Sure there will be the occasional time that we go back to kill it as new member comes in but it would not be an every day occurance or every spawn occurance ... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, other guilds would never see the mob.  We’re not talking about a guild of 20-30 people mobilizing quickly, we are talking about xp groups of L 65s that would make Sev regret having spawned, and the guilds that were once on rotation regret having taken him off.  There would be no “moving on”, and it wouldn’t be some misperceived threat by the “big guilds” doing this as policy.  It would be small groups figuring out how to best spend their plat on their new frog twinks, at the expense of the guilds that actually find CoFs and Warrior epics useful.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Yes I can understand the fact that you are trying to be fair to the smaller guilds ... But I see it as more of a bottleneck , and hinderance ...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don’t think you do, but welcome to the larger guild’s end of the RTA compromise.  For every rotation you find a “hindrance”, think, really think, about just how many mobs BOTS or Tindi or NB has held back on not killing that they easily could have if this server were 100% FCFS.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And again guilds that claim &quot;well, if there isn't a rotation , we'll just kill em all the time &quot; .... This is not in disagreement ... What is in disagreement with those that state this , is that they are doing so , as a tactic and ploy , cause the longer some of the rotations stay , the fewer guilds they have to contend with.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, it’s not a plot or a tactic.  You have some very grave misconceptions of what your new “guild capabilities” would be, if suddenly you had uncontested access to Sev and Trak, that all of a sudden you’d jump right on King Tormax, Lord Yelinak, or Avatar of War rotations. . .rotations that BOTS has had on autopass for more than 6 months.  So no, the Sev rotation and Trak rotation are not what keep BOTS or Tindi, or LoM from having competition.  The Sev and Trak rotations make sure that the guilds who are interested in AND capable of killing them, can do so much more often than if they weren’t on rotation.  Once every 3 months is certainly better than never.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>My main contestation with Rotations , is A) How many guilds exist on a few of them ... Again see my point above ... I don't see a problem with a Guild getting several kills in a row , and getting it out of their system , and done with ... they will move on ... And the Bottleneck will eventually dissapate... As it stands now ... the Bottlenecks continue to grow. And B) All these little sub hidden rules that aren't stated on different rotations ...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There is no “getting it out of your system”, guilds leave rotations when the loot gained from an encounter is no longer useful for the time invested.  Guilds that are on rotations, usually, have more members, and thus have more people who want and can use the gear from the mobs they do.  If Item X is good for all your healers, does it not stand to reason that all your healers might want it?  If one Item X drops every two slayings on average, and you have Y healers, you will have to kill Mob A 2Y times, in order to get everyone taken care of (assuming no turnover).  Again, the more people that want said content, the greater the need for a rotation to share it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If everyone that has ever left my guild , with most all of them being people that I wouldn't mind being tagged , were to still be in my Guild ... I probably wouldn't be here today posting this big huge long reply ... Instead my Guild would be planesable , we would be on different rotations etc ... But thats a big if ... and they aren't , and I am ...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So its ok for you to look after your own interests, but anyone else who does so is being unfair?  As for losing people to bigger guilds, welcome to being a guild leader.  We all lose people, and its no easier for BOTS to get good quality people who won’t get burned out raiding 7 nights a week as it is for you to get 40 good, quality players L 46+.  As for your focus on planar reservations: The only use for Hate/Fear/Sky is for epic items, the armor in Kael arena or PoG is much more powerful than PoH/PoF armor, and can be farmed by 1-2 groups of L 55+.  Additionally, there are so few dates during the week that are reserved, that you should have no trouble getting to the planes if you felt so inclined.  However, I don’t see why you keep bringing up planar reservations in a discussion about PoP flag mobs.  Planar reservations have nothing to do with rotations and nothing to do with PoP.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This is why the Rules and laws that we all go by must be looked at from time to time ... Do I want to see a million rules no ... Do I want the ones that are in existance to be more clear about things , yes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What unclear rules?  I don’t see any.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I don't think that the dispute is whether or not the mob is a canidate for rotation ... The Dispute is that the mob is being treated like a rotation when it is not. If this mob were rotation , I don't think this thread would even be in existance.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Right, so while hiding behind a technicality of the written rules, you ignore the spirit that went into their creation:  That we share content amongst those able to kill said content. . .on their own.  Putting AD on rotation just hurts those middle and up-and-coming guilds who would benefit from repeated tries, all because the guilds that don’t stand a chance against him on their own, insist on taking advantage of this technicality.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grommofbots>Gromm of BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blood of the Spider</span><br>  Posts: 341<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/8/03 1:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=646.topic&index=142>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Response to Teamwork thread in guild rep forum.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>IF I'm in a Guild (note I'm making an example)and we have the man power and mobolization to go take out a mob fast, sure for a while , we will probably do just that ... And Yes other Guilds might not see the mob for a while ... But eventually other guilds will because my Guild will loose interest in the mob as its something that we no longer need , and we will move on ... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So, by using your example, IF your guild wanted to kill Trakanon 40 times and could get to it first all 40 times, then it is ok for all the other guilds to not have access to Trakanon for 120 days.  Followed by another guild that wants to do the same thing.  So, if you are in a 5th guild, you may have to wait 4 * 120 = 480 days (a year and a half) before you can see Trakanon.  But... that's ok because you got yours.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>But I see it as more of a bottleneck , and hinderance ... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, it is a hinderance to your guild to have to share.  But using your example, you shifted the hinderance from your guild to being the hinderance for all others.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So yes there does come a point in time when rotations become a bad thing .... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So you suggest FFA is better?  See the above.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What is in disagreement with those that state this , is that they are doing so , as a tactic and ploy , cause the longer some of the rotations stay , the fewer guilds they have to contend with. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Why is this surprising?  The longer the game goes, the more people who will be able to do stuff.  It is simple common sense.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>My main contestation with Rotations , is A) How many guilds exist on a few of them ... Again see my point above ... I don't see a problem with a Guild getting several kills in a row , and getting it out of their system , and done with ... they will move on ... And the Bottleneck will eventually dissapate... As it stands now ... the Bottlenecks continue to grow. And B) All these little sub hidden rules that aren't stated on different rotations ... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Your main concern is self-centered.  As long as you get yours, screw the rest.  &quot;Several kills in a row&quot; is not how it usually works.  My guild killed Trakanon around 50 times to equip our members before we &quot;got it out of our system&quot;.  What you suggest is FCFS which will revert to racing and all of the issues we had to face before.  Meanwhile, while YOU are getting your 50 Trakanons, all the other guilds must wait 1/2 a year for you to &quot;get it out of your system&quot;, during which time they see zero Trakanons.  Why should you keep them out that long when they are able to do the content?<br>
<br>
[a bunch of stuff about the number for PoFear/PoHate access]<br>
<br>
a) On an off day, go to the planes all you want.  All that number is for is to *reserve* a date.  As I understand it (haven't checked in a long time), PoFear and PoHate are reserved less than once or twice a week.  There is *nothing* that keeps you out during that time.<br>
<br>
b) It has already been mentioned that there probably isn't going to be much resistance to changing that value.  All it takes is for someone who is concerned about it to get off their ass and do something about it.  Call a meeting and such (probably wouldn't last 15 minutes) to get the number changed down to 18 or something.  Constantly coming to the board and bitching about it does not get it changed.<br>
<br>
As far as other rotations go, there is no limit on the folks you take.  If you can kill the AoW with your guild, which consists of 20 people, then you can get on the rotation.  If it takes you 100, then you can still get a rotation slot.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Trakanon: You kill him to get a couple items and some keys that allow you to go to another zone you couldn't otherwise - it spawns every three days (or whatever).<br>
Aerin Dar: You kill him to get a couple items and some keys that allow you to go to another zone you couldn't otherwise - it spawns every three days (or whatever).<br>
<br>
Explain the difference.<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
One is an established rotation mob ... the other is not. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
...and the only difference between an &quot;established rotation mob&quot; and one that isn't is the simple fact that *a* guild (meaning any one guild/group) that has killed the thing has not asked for a rotation on it.  As soon as one asks for a rotation, then it is an &quot;established rotation mob&quot;, too.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I don't think that the dispute is whether or not the mob is a canidate for rotation ... The Dispute is that the mob is being treated like a rotation when it is not. If this mob were rotation , I don't think this thread would even be in existance. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Will it help clear things up if BotS asks for a rotation on AD?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I've seen more than one instance of people approaching this in different manners ... and most of them have run right smack into the brick wall , that I'm trying to deal with. Again see the thread that I linked up above. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The brick wall = their ass stuck to a couch.  I've already stated (as have others) that you won't get it done on this board with 100 people saying different things.  Talk to people, formulate something cohesive.  Then propose it.  You need exactly one proposal coming from a group of people - not 200 posts from 100 different people.  If you can do it offline, that's fine.  Use IRC or whatever to discuss it.  If you can't get folks together from RTA to vote on it, just post a clean thread with the title &quot;Proposal To Change the Number of Folks Required to Reserve A Plane Date&quot;.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Actually I know exactly what I'm doing .... and it is exactly what I need to be doing , and is resulting in the type of response that I was hoping for ... Whether my other posts indicate this or not , is a moot point, as revealing everything would defeat my own purpose. <br>
<br>
