And this is exactly why your statement is a contradiction.  Lots of guilds wanting to be on a rotation = highly contested.  Do some simple math, using your statement:  <br>
1.  Most guilds want them to go back to FFA.<br>
2.  Most guilds believe that they could get 2-3 FFA kills in before their rotation comes up.<br>
<br>
Simple math shows this as an impossibility.  Supposed 1/2X + 1 of the guilds (which is a simple majority where X is the total number of guilds - thus your most simple 'most') want the rotations to go FFA on those two mobs.  If this same 'most' believe that they can get even 2 FFA kills during the same duration that they could get 1 kill under rotation, that would mean that the mob would have spawned 2 times more than it could have by the mechanics of the game (1/2X + 1) * 2 = X + 2.  Added to that, even if half the guilds could get in twice the number of kills, that means that the other half of the guilds on rotation would get none (zero).  I guess that is ok though to you - might makes right in your opinion, clearly stated by your post.  This is exactly what you accuse the higher tier guilds of and as being such a terrible crime.  You also are most likely incorrect in assuming that your guild would be one of the ones that actually could kill the mob more times during what was once the rotational period (oops, didn't think about that did you?)<br>
