Yes.  Twice.  Your assertion is that this whole thing is about keeping other guilds out of “our zones”.  I merely pointed out that you’re wrong, it’s not “just about keeping other guilds out”, and offered three examples of guilds that got in and not one word of it came up here.  No one is threatening to permakill anything, they are *showing you* that if their aim was to keep people out, they would have done so, but, and here is the tough part to understand, they haven’t.  Thus, your “voila” proof that this is all about keeping the “newbs” out is wrong.  It’s about playing on an even playing field, and alliances are ok, but they have to be all or nothing, not pick and choose at whim.  I’m not twisting anything you’re saying, I’m saying that what you’re saying is not accurate.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> I am having a hard time even coming up with a response to this. Fair Play???? As defined by who? YOU??? So now we smaller guilds not only have to abide by SoE's rules, RTA Rules (that you made), but we also have to make sure we don't break the imaginary Karadin-made &quot;Fair Play&quot; policy. But I don't really want to get into this again with you Karadin. This is where we differ about as much as two humans can. You believe that because you have defeated a mob - You get to set the rules and policies about how all other guilds kill that said mob. I completely disagree.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
