So you’ve asked every player L 1 – 65 for their input into their thoughts on all the rotations your guild is on, and what their ideas are on PoP mobs and teaming, right?  No, obviously you haven’t, nor should you.  I don’t make a single comment about the Shei rotation, as my guild has never killed him.  I have no right to comment on the special rules that govern it, and I won’t listen to someone who hasn’t killed Emperor tell me or the guilds on the rotation how we should change it.  I don’t believe because I have defeated a mob that I get to set rules and policies on HOW other guilds kill that said mob.  If you wanna use a ranger or bard for MT, or wanna use a cleric nuking rotation, go for it, I don’t care.  What I do believe is that because we entered into the RTA rotations with the understanding that each side gives and takes (small guilds and large), that if those smaller guilds are going to change their portion of that compromise, then it makes no sense for the larger guilds to continue to make theirs.  If you need an alliance to beat your top end content, then do so, but be an alliance for all rotations, or don’t kill your falsely inflated top end content.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Rotations work when the benefit a majority of guilds over a minority. That is why Rots like Sev and Trak are becoming obselete, because they now have more Guilds on the rotation then Guilds wanting to get on the rotation. I bet most guilds on those rotations would want them to go back to FFA. I think they probably believe in the time it takes for their turn to come up on those rotations, that they could probably get 2-3 FFA kills in. But any decision made on these two rotations should only be made by those guilds currently killing him - Guilds that have passed on to higher content who no longer kill these mobs should have NO say in what happens to these decisions. It does not affect them. So the majority are the guilds on the Rotation, thus no benefit.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
