The only rotations that have become obsolete are THO and Burrower, because no one took the time to kill him.  Tunare is getting there, because no one wants to clear PoG.  Any rotation with 20+ guilds on it however, has never been more relevant in its lifetime.  Any guild that thinks they would get “2-3” FFA kills is fooling itself.  If either of those mobs went off rotation, all that would happen is no guild currently on rotation would ever see him again, but the upside is they could buy said green scales or CoF or Torpor in the bazaar from the xp groups of the larger guilds who would take it upon themselves to kill Sev at every opportunity to equip their twinks.  Please notice, Talendor and Gorenaire are never up.  Ever.  I’m not talking about a threat from the GL of BOTS or NB or Tindi, I’m talking about the same people that made the Manaburn Syndicate tick.  A simple xp group porting in, whacking a 32k hp dragon and looting him, before the 25 – 30 members of the former rotation guild had even finished porting.  The more people interested in one mob, the more a rotation is needed, not less.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> But any decision made on these two rotations should only be made by those guilds currently killing him - Guilds that have passed on to higher content who no longer kill these mobs should have NO say in what happens to these decisions. It does not affect them. So the majority are the guilds on the Rotation, thus no benefit.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
