<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Flagged mob rotations don't benefit anyone except those that have already got their flags. (And right now - That is a Minority) Now..If the case was that AD, Behemoth, Grummus were getting permakilled by guilds that have already kill them and thus denying other guilds the opportunity to kill them, then yes..a rotation would be warranted. But we know that is not the case - Maybe it will be a case in the future, but then the decision on whether to make them a rotation mob should be only between those guilds that are still killing them (and really those guilds that are still trying to do or will so in the near future). BotS, Tindi, NB, etc should have no say in what happens to those mobs because you are no longer currently killing them. So why would you have a right to decide when you aren't even interested in killing them? Just because you kill them first??<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
