No, they only have no benefit for the guilds that have killed him already because the guilds that can kill Aerin Dar easily are VT-capable guilds (BOTS, NB, Tindi).  Those guilds that can kill him, but just barely, do find his items useful, but it’s too close of a fight and takes too long to form up for, to risk killing him on a regular basis.  Then you have the guilds that team him, whose items are in no way comparable to his drops, but can’t beat on their own.  Please, if all he is about is flags, tell me that CB and VOLS destroyed whatever two items dropped.  I would offer that not only did they not destroy them, but those are now amongst, if not the, premiere items in their respective guilds.  As for why we should have a say?  We have comments to make because the server conventions of how we function are being undermined, it’s the principle of the thing.  And if you think NB is done with Aerin Dar, could you please tell my two members and our four recent applicants who don’t have the flags that?  I would also point out, we have killed Aerin Dar no less than seven times.  Our next time will be our eighth kill.  “Guilds will only kill him 2-3 times and move on”  I guess not.<br>
