<br>
I have no problem being wrong, if you knew me in person, you'd know this.  Goodness knows I'm wrong often enough.  However, what you have is a small handfull of people who are responding to this thread saying &quot;teh rotations is teh suck on AD&quot;.  Up until now, the vast majority of the server thinks that rotations are, at worst, a necessary evil that we need to have.  All of a sudden, a mob appears that's only circumstantial difference is that you can kill it or quest it, your option, to get something it drops.  (Actually, this is not new either... Dain and the Tri-hackle gold-plated walnut cracker.)  In this case, it is a key that opens a door.<br>
<br>
So, the issue is that<br>
a) because the mob drops a key, and<br>
b) because you can also quest the key<br>
c) then the mob must have different rules<br>
<br>
c) does not necessarily follow a) + b) here<br>
<br>
<br>
Let me be very clear here:  to be very honest, I don't have a problem saying those mobs are FFA at all and that you can use everyone on the server plus your dog plus your mother-in-law to kill it.  However, I am not so quick to rush in and just say that &quot;sure, let's make em FFA&quot; without considering the other consequences such as the precedent it will set.  Yes, folks say &quot;it's only for this mob&quot; - famous last words.  I have no reason to believe that this isn't the first step in trying to extrapolate this reasoning onto other mobs.  It's what you call &quot;getting your foot in the door&quot;.  Once you open that can of worms, it's very difficult to put the lid back on.  (that enough cliches for you?)  Once you have this precedent, there is little to keep it from being used to extend it to everything else in the game.  Remember that in Law (such as real-life courts and stuff) precedence carries a *huge* weight in the interpretation of the laws and future/related laws and there are very clear reasons why this happens other than simply being some sort of procedure in the absense of others.  It's called logic and reasoning - which apply to all things whether it is  real life or discussions concerning actions in a game.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;Extrapolation&quot; and &quot;Convention&quot; ...these are the methods we will use to dictate server policy from now on. Get with the program, or /movelog, those are your two choices.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You are wrong.  These are what have always set policy.  The first &quot;official&quot; rotation was Trakanon.  When Talendor was killed, the rules for the Trakanon rotation were extrapolated to extend to Talendor (basically it was search-n-replace &quot;Trakanon&quot; with &quot;Talendor&quot; and *poof* you have the new rules).  As each mob was considered for rotation, the previous rules were simply extrapolated to cover them.  Now, there were a few other instances such as ToV-N where entrance to the rotation was secured simply by only killing Arryonyar - but you had to kill Arryonyar before you killed any other dragon back there.  Also, because of the undertaking, rules were required for extended stays - you get 48 hours to clear all of ToV-N or you pass what you haven't killed.<br>
<br>
By your logic, we should reconsider that rule of 48 hours since PoP is out now (2 expansions past ToV-N) and say that relative power has made the rotation so that you have to kill everything in 4 hours or pass, instead of 48.  I would imagine that folks wouldn't be happy about that.<br>
<br>
Another point, RTA hasn't in the past sanctioned rotions (remember, when I say this, it means that all the guilds agree to have a rotation on the mob) on mobs that you can kill with a single group, no matter how often they spawn.  Trakanon, Severilous, and a few others all fall into this category.  However, because of what they do represent, the majority in RTA still agrees to rotations on these mobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Welcome to the BoTS-NB server ...most of us refer to it as The Rathe.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Calling this statement &quot;idiotic&quot; is about the best compliment I can give to it.  You simply have no idea how anything on this server works so you make statements such as this seeking to gain some form of popularity with some group for your &quot;bucking the system&quot;.<br>
<br>
BotS doesn't really care one way or the other about many of the mobs that are currently on rotation.  We show how much we care by being on the rotation for it or by actively killing the mobs.  We have nothing to gain or lose by saying that AD/Grummus/etc are or are not FFA.  However, opening the door for team effort on these mobs simply opens the door for team effort on everything else in the game - from Trakanon up to the PoTime.  THAT is what we are concerned about.<br>
<br>
Again, your pleas of &quot;only for this mob&quot; do little to persuade because precedent is much stronger than this simple phrase.  Your promises with &quot;pretty please with sugar on top&quot; are not sufficient to convince me, or anyone, that we aren't getting on the edge of a slippery slope.<br>
<br>
If you cannot see our side of the argument then we are at an impass.  I assure you that we see yours and take it into consideration when we form our opinion on the matter.  You need to convince me (and others) that this isn't simply a foot in the door.  I will say that the qualification (similar to what has been given already) of something like:<br>
<br>
Mobs that enable entry into further zones when killed - whether by dropping an item which enables entry either directly or by completing a quest for such a key, giving character flags, or by any other means not specifically mentioned here - that can also be bypassed by quests that provide an alternate path to entry to the further zones but the quest does not require killing said mob to complete the alternate-path quest, which also have been proven to not stir any interest because of other items that they may drop and, because of this, have been proven to remain &quot;up&quot; for long periods of time, are open to FFA rules.<br>
<br>
is a little better. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grommofbots>Gromm of BotS</A> at: 4/9/03 10:21:46 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a> <b>8</b> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=181&stop=200>10</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=201&stop=220>11</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=221&stop=240>12</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=241&stop=260>13</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=261&stop=280>14</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showMessageRange?topicID=646.topic&start=281&stop=300>15</a><a href=http://pub6.ezboard.